gner":0,"boardgamehonor":0,"boardgamecategory":3,"boardgamemechanic":2,"boardgameexpansion":8,"boardgameversion":1,"expandsboardgame":0,"boardgameintegration":1,"contains":0,"containedin":0,"reimplementation":0,"reimplements":0,"boardgamefamily":4,"videogamebg":0,"boardgamesubdomain":0,"boardgameaccessory":2,"cardset":1},"secondarynamescount":0,"alternatenamescount":0,"primaryname":{"nameid":"2412782","name":"Kabuto Sumo: Sakura Slam","sortindex":"1","primaryname":"1","translit":"Kabuto Sumo: Sakura Slam"},"alternatenames":[],"description":"<p>It's cherry blossom season. As the beautiful sakura petals fall, a calm tranquility lingers in the air. It's the perfect calm before the storm: welcome to the <em><strong>Sakura Slam!</strong></em></p>\n\n<p>In this standalone sequel to <em>Kabuto Sumo</em>, players return as the wrestling Kabutomushi (&quot;helmet bugs&quot;) and compete to knock off their opponents on an all-new square arena. The coin-pushing mechanic returns, but with a new platform, characters, pillars, and powers.</p>\n\n<p>New Arena Features:</p>\n\n<ul>\n    <li>Notched Pushing Platform - In<em> Sakura Slam</em>, you must push from the corners of the arena. That makes it harder to focus completely on defense, as you can&rsquo;t always push your piece away from the edge&mdash;this means less stalemates and more body slams.</li>\n    <li>Fixed corners - Four fixed corner posts loom over each match. Using these posts, can you better predict how an aggressive maneuver will play out? Alternatively, if you&rsquo;re near the edge: can you &ldquo;rope-a-dope&rdquo; and use the post defensively?</li>\n    <li>Tagging Corners - When you push from a corner you haven&rsquo;t pushed from before, you place a marker, &quot;tagging&quot; that corner. Place one on each of the four posts to take a second push action immediately.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>All but two characters are compatible with the original <em>Kabuto Sumo</em>.</p>\n\n","wiki":"<span class='text-muted'>This p